headline: What Is the Best High-Yield Dividend Stock to Buy for Passive Income?
summary: Realty Income's real estate portfolio produces very stable cash flow to cover its high-yielding monthly dividend.  The REIT has a fortress-like financial profile.  It has lots of ways to continue growing its portfolio, which should support continued dividend increases.

headline: The Smartest High-Yield Stocks to Buy With $1,000 Right Now
summary: Dividend investors are saddled with a market that offers a paltry 1.2% dividend yield on the S&P 500.  Brookfield Asset Management has a 3.2% yield and is projecting strong dividend growth ahead.  Realty Income has a 5.6% yield and a three-decade-long history of reliably growing its dividend.
